data.enText: the man that Christians believe is the son of God and on whose teachings the Christian religion is based
a swear word that many people find offensive, used to show that you are angry, annoyed or surprised

data.chText: 天哪！看看时间，我迟到了！
data.enText: Christ! Look at the time─I'm late!

value.def: Christ is one of the names of Jesus, whom Christians believe to be the son of God and whose teachings are the basis of Christianity.
Some people say 'Christ!' when they are surprised, shocked, or annoyed, or in order to emphasize what they are saying. This use could cause offence.

example.ex: He looked at her watch. 'Christ! We only have three minutes!'
example.tran: 他看了看她的表：“天哪！我们仅剩3分钟了！”

value.tran: (表示震惊、生气等，或加强语气，可能具冒犯意味)天哪！
